<h3>It can be hard to give upward feedback, but development leads to better outcomes for all</h3>
<p>It can be difficult to give upward feedback, especially if you're worried about how it may affect the company's view of you (even more so if this person is responsible for evaluating your performance - you may feel as though ‘relationship trumps feedback'). Resist these urges - remind yourself and them that development leads to better outcomes for all of us - and that you hope you can both learn from having what seems to be an uncomfortable conversation. You may even feel more likely to give feedback if you frame it as ‘an opportunity to explore the way they approached something</p>
